responses.text:
On the scene came Christ The Lord, not with peace but with a sword.
He cleft the silent centuries, as ancient scrolls implored.
His sandals struck the roads of doubt, His mantle flicked the night;
He called the weary out of sleep, and summoned them to fight.

Not with the clash of metal arms, nor with the blood of war,
But with a word that sundered pride and opened every door.
He did not bring the easy calm, nor soothe the feeble will;
He lit a fire in trembling hearts, and bade them to be still.

So tremors shook the temple stones, the mighty and the meek;
For peace that cost no courage was never His to seek.

Please spare me your secrets—let them curl in your chest;
Not every confession deserves to be blessed.
I have my own shadows, my own hidden rooms;
Let mystery linger, let silence resume.

Your truths may be thunder, or delicate thread,
But I find my comfort in what’s left unsaid.
Please spare me your secrets, don’t burden my night;
Some things in the darkness should stay out of sight.
